Privacy Policy – Sleep Timer (Chrome Extension)

Effective date: February 14, 2026

1. Overview

Sleep Timer is a Chrome extension that displays the time remaining until a user-defined alarm time.
This extension operates entirely locally within the user's browser.

2. Data Collection
Sleep Timer does not collect, store, transmit, or share any personal information.
The extension does not collect:
Personally identifiable information
Health information
Financial information
Authentication data
Location data
Web history
User activity
Website content

3. Local Storage
The extension uses Chrome's storage API to save the user’s selected alarm time locally within the browser.
This data:
Is stored only on the user’s device
Is not transmitted to any external servers
Is not accessible to the developer
Is used solely to restore the selected alarm time when the popup is reopened

4. Data Sharing
Sleep Timer does not sell, transfer, or share any user data with third parties.

5. Third-Party Services
This extension does not use analytics services, advertising networks, or external APIs.

6. Changes to This Policy
If the functionality of the extension changes in the future, this privacy policy will be updated accordingly.

7. Contact
If you have questions regarding this policy, you may contact:

